            "attributionText": "from the GNU version of the Collaborative International Dictionary of English.",
            "sourceDictionary": "gcide",
            "text": "A word, phrase, or sentence, by way of comment or explanation, inserted in, or attached to, a sentence which would be grammatically complete without it. It is usually inclosed within curved lines (see def. 2 below), or dashes.",
